A single field whose value alone is wider than the 80-column budget: no break
can bring its own line under budget. The pass still breaks the literal once —
onto its own line, unconditionally, once the flat form doesn't fit, mirroring
prettier — then stops rather than looping forever re-discovering the same
over-long line. The golden below STILL contains an over-long line (the detail
field). That is correct: the guarantee this case pins is TERMINATION, not
"leave the literal alone" — an unsplittable field is broken once, same as a
splittable one, and the pass only refuses a SECOND round once breaking again
would not be progress.

-- input.gsx --
package ui

var errMsg = errInfo{detail: "zzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz"}
-- fmt.golden --
package ui

var errMsg = errInfo{
	detail: "zzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz",
}
